Regulatory Affairs Associate - 	Fixed – term contract of 1 year
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/05 06:55:53
Ref. JB3047348
Job Description
This position consists on preparing and compiling registration files and artworks for submissions;Interactive and efficient coordination of Life cycle maintenance activities
Major Accountabilities
:
•	Prepare, review and maintain documentation to support Regulatory submissions of new applications, variations and renewals.
•	Maintain and apply working knowledge of current and proposed regulations & guidelines pertaining to new applications, variations and renewals
•	Handle maintenance activities of registered products (variations) in coordination with IRA department and local distributors (company name change project).
•	Prepare and review labeling and artworks in coordination with our local distributors, graphic designer and manufacturing sites.
•	Review and compile the M1 in cooperation with IRA department and local distributors to fulfill the local requirements
•	Track status and progress of regulatory documentation.
•	Compile and prepare responses to regulatory authorities questions
•	Review of promotional material
•	Monthly reporting, regular and accurate updating of the tracking tools (database).
•	Regular archiving of registration files and related documents.
•	Handle special projects as determined by business needs.
Skills
Language:
English / Arabic
•Technical systems skills (. word processing, spreadsheets, databases, online research)
•Proofreading and editing skills
•Ability to contribute to multiple projects from a regulatory affairs perspective
•Ability to multitask and prioritize
